4️⃣ Difference between data= and json=
data=	                                                       json=
Sends form-encoded data	                                    Sends JSON data
Content-Type → application/x-www-form-urlencoded	        Content-Type → application/json
You must convert dict to JSON manually sometimes	        Automatically converts dict to JSON

Example:

requests.post(url, data=payload)   # Form data
requests.post(url, json=payload)   # JSON data (recommended for APIs)